name: I/O Extended 2017 Limbe
description: Join us remotely take part in the Google's annual flagship conference, I/O 2017. With a lot of changes across Google's ecosystem; Android, Cloud, Firbase, Chrome, Tensor Flow and other open source libraries you are bound to find something interesting.

name: Njaka Africa Code Week 2017
description:
GDG Limbe is partnering with Njaka.org to organize Njaka Africa Code Week 2017.

We are inviting all kids aged 11-17 to join us for an intro to computer science. You do not need to come with a PC as we will provide them.

There are two tracks to choose from based on your interest:

- Develop a game with Scratch
- Build a website with JS/HTML/CSS

name: DevFest Fako 2017
description:
The DevFest Fako 2017 event is a three-days-long hack-streak aimed at getting students, developers and entrepreneurs from GDGs in Fako (GDG Buea and GDG Limbe ) to learn Google's technologies such as Firebase, Cloud And Tensorflow and use them to build a PWA utilising Firebase Cloud and Offline-first functions. We intend to develop this PWA during a two-day Firebase AppFest at Skylabase Inc.

More Info:Â https://www.meetup.com/preview/GDG-Buea/events/243045998

name: Limbe Local Guides Meetup
description: Techies and map lovers in and around Limbe will be meeting at the Zuoix office. Situated on the second floor of PressBook building in half Mile Limbe to discuss and update important aspects of the mapping situation in and around Fako.

name: Web Application Development Workshop
description: Free two-day hands-on workshop on HTML5, CSS3, Javascript, and PHP. We will also cover some Google services for web application developers like Google Cloud Platform, Google Maps and Forms. Trainers are Paul Mbua (CEO of Zixtech Organisation) Fongoh Tayong (Developer of DigitalRenter.com) and Zuo Bruno (CEO of Zuoix).

name: I/O Extended 2018 Limbe
description: I/O Extended 2018 Limbe brings developers from around Limbe to take part in the awesomeness of Google I/O via talks, hands-on learning with experts, and a first look at Google's latest developer products.

name: Walk Through on Firebase
description: This is an Intro to Google FireBase Event. Here we would walk through the basics of Firebase. This event will be live through the channel https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=chUImLIQqD0. Follow through and practice

name: DevFest + Firebase Limbe 2018
description: Bring along laptops for this event and for we would have live demos on Google's technologies such as Firebase, Cloud, and Tensorflow and use them to build befitting apps. During the event, we would have multiple talks on Cloud, Machine Learning with Tensorflow and also, we would have a code lab to build an app with Firebase technology.
